Logic: That pain in your right side is your enlarged liver, by the way. As for your kidneys... you've really been compounding the damage lately.
You: Why?
You: These are my just desserts. I will endure this pain with *dignity*.
Pain Threshold: And there's a lot of it. Ever present in your organs. It's like every one of them has their own *nasty* song to sing.
Variable["doomed.radiocomputer_counted_headless"] == true
You: I'm sorry, cells! It's all me! It's my fault!
Limbic System: *Now* you're finally thinking about something other than yourself. Let's see how far that'll get you.
Ancient Reptilian Brain: Sure, you do. They're all so friendly, aren't they?
Volition: Some of them are. Some of them are nice. Others are scared.
Ancient Reptilian Brain: Oh yeah, baby. Frame your suffering as a masterpiece. Only one problem -- no one's watching. It's boring, buddy, boring as death.
Ancient Reptilian Brain: You're just stuck here. In the half-world. Could try looking at other people. *Really* looking. But why would you want to start doing that?
Volition: Come now. Humans have earned your trust. And you theirs...
Untitled hub
Drama: Thou art honourable and just, sire. 'Tis the snakes who are vile! Hissing in the grass...
Ancient Reptilian Brain: You had your chance, Harry-boy, and you missed it. Started thrashing around, acting all brave -- now the Dark Centre has vanished. You'll never get back to it.
Empathy: Maybe if you weren't so hard on yourself...
Limbic System: Yes, your body is a system, and and it's failing you because you're failing it.

Ancient Reptilian Brain: There's no dignity here... only reflections of your body mass. Flashes of the day. You keep coming back to yourself in the mirror -- but why? To admire all your *accomplishments*?
You: I thought I was on the express to The Silence!

Ancient Reptilian Brain: Now, you've gone off the rails, baby, now you're stuck sitting here by the tracks, admiring the wreck around you. You just can't help it: looking at yourself, the sum total of your *accomplishments*...
You: I will! I'm looking at people all the time. I like them.
You: This body's worthless anyway... no one does anything nice to it.
Limbic System: ...But it never seems to let *you* go, does it? Time to rise and wipe that shining sweat off as best you can. Gather your bearings. Rock and roll.
Electrochemistry: Maybe if you... you know... like... TOOK A LOT OF DRUGS? Before you go to sleep. That'd do the trick...
Endurance: Women. It's the women. Look out for the women. They're *oathbreakers*...
You: I'm an artist and liver damage is my art.
Untitled hub
You: Human beings will *always* betray you.
You: [Open your eyes.]
Ancient Reptilian Brain: How many promises have *you* kept lately, Sir Harry? To the great, see-through world, the tenderness?
Perception (Sight): People are beautiful. Statuesque. Parodies and tragedies of themselves. A great democracy of creatures...
Empathy: Every cell in your body is moaning in agony, asking, "What did we ever do to you?"

Ancient Reptilian Brain: Oh yes. *They'll* check you out, give you some pills, make it all okay. The wonder-makers.
Logic: Maybe if you cracked the damn thing, then you'd feel satisfied and tired. Holding the picture puzzle in your hands... complete!
You: Just get me out of here then. Back to the other place.
Ancient Reptilian Brain: Let it! Let it!
Limbic System: Here we are again, my broken bird. The waves are coming... carrying you away... but you can't go. No -- you have to stay. Always half-aware of yourself.

Limbic System: It's your disgusting *body*. Even through your sleep, you feel a vague discomfort suffusing it. Your belly and your sides are unpleasantly tender. You wish you could curl up into a foetal ball of safety, but you cannot -- because of the PAIN.
Drama: Put on your prettiest face for the masses!
Limbic System: And why might *that* be the case? What love alights on such a bloated corpse-to-be?
You: It's all the system's fault. The system failed me.
You: Wait, wasn't this the express to Fuck-All-Borough?
Limbic System: Oh, baby boy. You're already *in* the other place. There's no nourishment for you tonight. Maybe tomorrow?
Rhetoric: At least they're *interesting*. Each one has a process just like yours, running in the space between their ears, full of secrets.
You: Hey, what is this? I was on the express to Zero-Holm!
Limbic System: You're not *cooperating* brother-man.
You: I think I... need medical attention.
Variable["doomed.radiocomputer_counted_headless"] == true

Limbic System: Don't be stupid Harry, it's not happening. They don't make new *kidneys* and *livers* in hospital. All you've got to do is pray to god it passes -- while you *stare* at the flickering darkness.
You: No, please... Where is that blessed nothingness? That sweet oblivion?

Limbic System: What do you think you're doing right now? Coming to some greater awareness? Look at all these lights! Blinking in and out of existence -- *thoughts*! You're just *pretending* that you're asleep, even to yourself. While the world goes on without you...
!(Variable["doomed.radiocomputer_counted_headless"] == true)
Logic: That pain in your right side is your enlarged liver, by the way. As for your kidneys... you've really been compounding the damage lately. And, trust me, you don't want me to do the maths.
Conceptualization: But this suffering -- it must have *some* kind of meaning... A story that will come out of it. Perhaps even a story that you will write yourself?
